! TODO: could return loc OR direction


! Overall plot explanation:
!
! Brother Hugh's sister, Rose, is under extreme financial pressure---her
! son needed surgery and she needs money desperately. To try to provide for
! her, Hugh began stealing illuminated manuscripts made by Brother Wilfred.
! Being so elderly, Wilfred and Oswald just assume Wilfred has misplaced
! them. Hugh has been communicating with an outsider, arranging to sell
! these works for money.
!
! Aelred (somehow) found out about this (perhaps related to the rosehips,
! since those would have come from the garden). He told Hugh he needed to
! confess, but instead Hugh poisoned him with the Henbane Decoction kept in
! the Infirmary. Aelred dies, but not before pointing to the rosebushes that
! line the Slype and also saying the cryptic phrase "One life for two".

! The player can recognise that Aelred was poisoned and recognise the poison
! was henbane, based on the symptoms Aelred has while he was dying. The
! player can find a letter from the buyer,
! as well as find letters from Rose about her plight.
! Ultimately, the player can get into the Undercroft and search it and
! find the most reason stolen psalter.
!
! There are four major pieces of evidence:
! - the letter from the buyer (explaining where the manuscripts went)
! - the letters from Rose (proving his need)
! - the coins hidden in the CryptVestry (proving the sale)
! - the stolen psalter
!
! Notes on dialog for Remigio: he's uneducated and speaks a mix of his
! native Italian and English.


! =============================================================================

Constant Story "Our Lady of Thorns";
Constant Headline
  "^An interactive monastic tragedy
  ^Copyright 2026 by Joel Burton^";
Release 1;

